	<title>Meta Module Examples</title>
	
	<para>The meta module controls the CLI service and sets its tunable parameters. This module
	does not use XML input or output. Structure of the output data is listed in
	<xref linkend="been.user.cli.reference.meta"/>.</para>
	
	<para>Get the request counter:</para>
	<screen>$ <emphasis role="strong">./bcmd meta counter</emphasis></screen>
	
	<para>Flush the instance pool for the <command>results</command> module:</para>
	<screen>$ <emphasis role="strong">./bcmd meta flush pool=results</emphasis></screen>
	
	<para>Flush all the module instance pools:</para>
	<screen>$ <emphasis role="strong">./bcmd meta flush all</emphasis></screen>
	
	<para>Switch to detailed debugging output style and back to normal output style:</para>
	<screen>$ <emphasis role="strong">./bcmd meta output debug</emphasis></screen>
	<screen>$ <emphasis role="strong">./bcmd meta output normal</emphasis></screen>
</sect3>